Brighton manager Oscar Garcia has offered his resignation following his side's play-off defeat to Derby.

The Seagulls' promotion hopes were dashed following their crushing loss against Steve McClaren's side.

And Sportsmail understands the manager, who only arrived at Brighton last summer, has told the club he wants to leave.

